WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:04.958
[pages riffling]

00:08.000 --> 00:11.000
♪ dramatic music playing ♪

00:11.000 --> 00:14.000
♪

00:17.000 --> 00:20.500
♪

00:26.500 --> 00:27.167
BRYCE: Okay,

00:27.167 --> 00:29.875
all we gotta to do is get through
the entire Tokyo Police Department,

00:29.875 --> 00:32.500
the Japanese Secret Service,
and a bunch of Special Forces dudes.

00:32.500 --> 00:33.333
[Monkey grunts]

00:33.333 --> 00:35.667
Oh, right, right, right.
Without killing any of them. Yeah.

00:35.667 --> 00:39.042
Then we gotta fight our way through
a couple insane Japanese superheroes.

00:39.042 --> 00:39.708
[grunts]

00:39.708 --> 00:41.500
No, I know, who aren't
our enemies. Yep.

00:41.500 --> 00:43.208
Then we gotta get
to the top of the tallest,

00:43.208 --> 00:45.417
most heavily defended building in Tokyo,

00:45.417 --> 00:48.917
probably uh, fight Lady Bullseye again,
who's already kicked your ass,

00:48.917 --> 00:51.792
and then, then, if we're
lucky enough to survive,

00:51.792 --> 00:53.583
kill your girlfriend's uncle.

00:54.167 --> 00:56.417
[whimpers, grunts]

00:56.417 --> 00:59.042
Look, look, look, look, don't worry.
She'll totally understand.

00:59.042 --> 01:00.708
I‐I know it's tough. Okay?

01:00.708 --> 01:03.792
I mean, she said you guys are family,
which means he's family.

01:03.792 --> 01:05.750
And‐and I've had
to kill family before,

01:05.750 --> 01:07.417
and yes, it sucks,

01:07.417 --> 01:09.042
but you know what's worse?

01:09.042 --> 01:09.958
[Monkey grunts]

01:10.500 --> 01:12.458
Actually, I‐I‐I don't know
what's worse.

01:12.792 --> 01:13.667
[Monkey sighs]

01:13.667 --> 01:15.958
Okay, uh, th‐this is
a terrible pep talk.

01:15.958 --> 01:17.375
Uh, here,
hold out your hands.

01:17.375 --> 01:18.375
[Monkey groans]

01:18.375 --> 01:19.667
Alright, you know what these are?

01:20.708 --> 01:21.792
Calluses.

01:21.792 --> 01:24.542
You're the best damn assassin
I've ever met, you're a monster. Okay?

01:24.542 --> 01:25.458
[Monkey grunts]

01:25.458 --> 01:28.125
And when we turn this corner,
we're gonna walk up to that building

01:28.125 --> 01:29.792
and you're gonna fulfill
your destiny.

01:30.292 --> 01:32.375
And then I'm gonna go

01:32.375 --> 01:34.000
wherever the hell I deserve to go.

01:34.667 --> 01:37.208
Just just two dudes.
Two fates.

01:37.625 --> 01:39.167
One awesome ride. Right?

01:39.625 --> 01:41.958
I don't know about you,
but I'd watch the shit outta that movie.

01:43.208 --> 01:44.750
[hoots]

01:45.542 --> 01:46.667
♪

01:47.417 --> 01:50.083
[crowd shouting]

01:50.083 --> 01:54.167
♪

02:02.125 --> 02:03.208
[whimpers]

02:03.208 --> 02:06.500
♪ dramatic theme playing ♪

02:06.500 --> 02:09.625
♪

02:15.542 --> 02:18.708
[crowd shouting]

02:26.458 --> 02:27.792
BRYCE: Psst.
‐ Huh?

02:27.792 --> 02:29.000
BRYCE: Hey, Yuki.

02:29.625 --> 02:31.125
Hey, over here.
[growls]

02:31.125 --> 02:32.583
It's me, Bryce Fowler?

02:32.917 --> 02:34.667
We met at the, uh,
the Love Motel, you know?

02:34.667 --> 02:36.667
We fought on top of a car.
You tried to kill me?

02:38.125 --> 02:39.917
[eerie moaning]

02:39.917 --> 02:41.042
You look great, by the way.

02:41.042 --> 02:43.458
I‐I‐I‐‐ Did you do something different
with your hair or something?

02:43.458 --> 02:45.083
I can't put my finger on it.

02:45.083 --> 02:46.625
[eerie moaning]
Right, right, right.

02:46.625 --> 02:49.042
Okay, uh, look, anyway,
I'm‐I'm‐I'm‐I'm here for Monkey?

02:50.125 --> 02:51.083
‐ Monkey?

02:51.083 --> 02:52.708
‐ Exactly, yeah, short guy,

02:52.708 --> 02:54.708
wears a suit,
little bit of a temper problem. Yeah.

02:54.708 --> 02:57.250
‐ Monkey is a noble warrior.

02:57.250 --> 03:01.583
He has my allegiance
if ever he were to call on Yuki!

03:01.583 --> 03:03.292
‐ Yeah, well, hey, ring‐ring.

03:04.042 --> 03:05.625
Hey, uh, will you grab Haruka?

03:05.875 --> 03:07.875
And meet us over in the alley
by the Burger King.

03:08.875 --> 03:11.167
♪

03:11.167 --> 03:13.083
HARUKA: What? That's impossible.

03:13.542 --> 03:14.917
Shinji?

03:14.917 --> 03:16.333
[screeches, hoots]

03:16.333 --> 03:18.917
‐ We thought so too,
but it actually makes perfect sense.

03:18.917 --> 03:20.667
‐ They thought so too,

03:20.667 --> 03:22.875
but it makes
perfect sense.

03:22.875 --> 03:25.667
‐ But that would mean‐‐

03:27.125 --> 03:28.542
This is all for nothing.

03:29.667 --> 03:31.000
Wait. What about Akiko?

03:31.333 --> 03:32.333
Is she involved too?

03:32.333 --> 03:34.500
[hoots, screeches]

03:34.833 --> 03:36.375
‐ Uh, no, no, no, no.
Akiko doesn't know.

03:36.375 --> 03:38.417
I mean, at least we hope
she doesn't.

03:38.417 --> 03:41.292
‐ Akiko is innocent.

03:41.292 --> 03:43.708
‐ Wait, how do you speak monkey?

03:44.125 --> 03:47.458
‐ I am speaking with the ghost
that's with the monkey.

03:47.792 --> 03:49.208
He speaks monkey.

03:49.583 --> 03:51.083
[hoots]
‐ Hold on,

03:51.875 --> 03:53.125
there's another ghost?

03:53.125 --> 03:54.458
‐ Oh yeah.

03:54.458 --> 03:55.958
And he's handsome
as all hell.

03:57.125 --> 03:59.792
HARUKA: [clears throat] Excuse me.
Clear the way. Coming through.

03:59.792 --> 04:01.750
Got a lot of hungry grunts
inside the building.

04:02.542 --> 04:06.042
‐ [muttering]:
Uh, I... I don't know.

04:08.000 --> 04:09.167
[grunts]

04:09.167 --> 04:10.292
[whimpers]

04:13.333 --> 04:15.500
‐ Stop right there.

04:15.500 --> 04:16.833
[both gasp]

04:20.000 --> 04:21.583
‐ I'll take one of those.

04:22.083 --> 04:24.750
‐ Uh... uh... sorry, sir...

04:25.417 --> 04:27.958
they're only for guests
inside the party.

04:27.958 --> 04:31.667
‐ Silver Samurai is the greatest hero
in all of Japan.

04:31.667 --> 04:33.958
‐ No! I'm just trying
to do my job.

04:33.958 --> 04:36.750
‐ Your only job is
to feed Silver Samurai!

04:36.750 --> 04:39.167
I have been standing
around here for hours,

04:39.167 --> 04:40.458
now give me
a frickin' rice cake!

04:41.625 --> 04:42.792
[Monkey screeches]

04:43.292 --> 04:44.333
SILVER SAMURAI: Huh?

04:44.333 --> 04:46.208
VENDOR: They made me do it!
They made me do it!

04:47.000 --> 04:48.542
‐ Ohhhh shit.

04:50.167 --> 04:52.125
[grunting]

04:52.958 --> 04:55.000
Yeah, I don't think it's gonna work
this time, bud.

04:55.208 --> 04:57.333
[Monkey screeching]

04:57.333 --> 04:58.583
MAN: Hey, look!

04:58.583 --> 05:00.750
The pigs are attacking
the monkey!

05:00.750 --> 05:01.792
Let's get 'em!

05:01.792 --> 05:04.833
[crowd shouting]

05:04.833 --> 05:07.333
‐ Huh?
SILVER SAMURAI: Everybody remain calm.

05:07.333 --> 05:09.917
Silver Samurai has everything
under control‐‐ [grunts]

05:09.917 --> 05:12.250
[people screaming]

05:12.917 --> 05:14.125
Traitors!

05:14.667 --> 05:16.458
I should have known.

05:16.458 --> 05:18.333
Protect the Prime Minister!

05:18.750 --> 05:20.125
[grunts]

05:22.167 --> 05:24.750
‐ Aw shit, shit, shit, shit.

05:24.750 --> 05:26.750
‐ Chaos on election night.

05:26.750 --> 05:28.750
Violence erupts
in downtown Tokyo,

05:28.750 --> 05:30.917
and we have reports
that the monkey vigilante

05:30.917 --> 05:32.917
that has been terrorizing
the city lately

05:32.917 --> 05:34.542
may be at the center of it.

05:34.542 --> 05:37.458
I repeat: the so‐called
"Hit Monkey"

05:37.458 --> 05:39.042
may be at the center
of it all.

05:39.458 --> 05:42.000
Authorities are saying
to seek safety and shelter‐‐

05:42.000 --> 05:43.417
‐ He's coming for me.

05:43.792 --> 05:44.917
I know it.

05:44.917 --> 05:46.417
‐ No, Uncle,

05:47.000 --> 05:48.625
he's one of the good guys.

05:48.625 --> 05:49.917
He's my friend.

05:49.917 --> 05:51.208
‐ What are you talking about?

05:52.000 --> 05:53.667
You know this creature?

05:53.667 --> 05:55.625
‐ Ozu was behind it all.

05:55.625 --> 05:57.208
He orchestrated
Ken's assassination

05:57.208 --> 05:58.500
and almost got me killed.

05:58.500 --> 06:00.250
He also tried
to steal the election

06:00.250 --> 06:01.792
from the rightful candidate.

06:01.792 --> 06:03.292
Ozu was a terrible man!

06:03.958 --> 06:06.750
‐ What do you mean... was?

06:07.250 --> 06:08.583
‐ Monkey took care of him.

06:09.208 --> 06:10.375
‐ Ah‐‐

06:10.375 --> 06:12.083
AKIKO: And Bonsai Master, too.

06:13.250 --> 06:14.417
‐ Oh my god.

06:14.417 --> 06:16.375
‐ Look, I know
it sounds crazy,

06:16.375 --> 06:18.708
but Monkey is coming here
to protect you.

06:19.083 --> 06:20.750
He's coming here
to protect us all.

06:21.458 --> 06:22.750
We just have to wait for him.

06:22.750 --> 06:23.708
[man gurgles]

06:24.458 --> 06:25.542
[coughs]

06:26.500 --> 06:28.083
♪

06:28.083 --> 06:30.458
‐ My thoughts exactly.

06:35.917 --> 06:37.458
[crowd shouting]

06:37.458 --> 06:39.333
[helicopter whirring]

06:43.708 --> 06:45.500
‐ End of the line, rodent!

06:47.208 --> 06:49.042
[grunts]

06:49.042 --> 06:50.375
[electricity crackles]

06:50.375 --> 06:52.417
‐ You mess with the Monkey,

06:52.708 --> 06:54.875
you get the Cobra.

06:54.875 --> 06:56.292
[hooting]
[Silver Samurai groans]

06:57.500 --> 06:59.250
‐ Hey, Fat Boy.

06:59.792 --> 07:01.333
I thought they locked you up.

07:02.042 --> 07:04.833
‐ Let me ask you:
how do you piss in that thing?

07:04.833 --> 07:06.125
Is there a cod‐piece?

07:06.125 --> 07:08.708
Or are you just free‐balling
under that skirt?

07:08.708 --> 07:10.958
‐ I'm obviously wearing pants!

07:10.958 --> 07:12.542
[yells]

07:14.292 --> 07:15.917
[groans]
[car alarm blaring]

07:16.875 --> 07:19.083
‐ [laughs] Too easy.

07:19.667 --> 07:22.250
‐ Holy shit. I love watching
weirdos duke it out!

07:22.250 --> 07:24.042
Feel like I'm watching
pay‐per‐view!

07:24.042 --> 07:25.250
You know?
For free, though!

07:25.667 --> 07:27.833
[hooting]

07:30.375 --> 07:32.208
[chuckles]

07:32.208 --> 07:33.667
‐ Okay, Monkey.

07:33.667 --> 07:36.167
One fastball special,
coming up.

07:36.167 --> 07:37.500
‐ Woo! Fastball special.

07:37.500 --> 07:39.417
Ha ha! Go ahead,
let 'em have it!

07:40.375 --> 07:41.375
[Fat Cobra grunts]

07:42.333 --> 07:46.750
♪

07:49.958 --> 07:50.625
‐ Huh?

07:51.458 --> 07:55.167
[screeching]

07:56.375 --> 08:00.125
♪

08:01.500 --> 08:03.125
‐ Ho‐ho, you again. Wow.

08:03.125 --> 08:04.875
I mean, it's funny how we keep
meeting like this, yeah?

08:04.875 --> 08:07.500
Must be fate. Right?
Or destiny?

08:09.792 --> 08:12.583
Yeah, you're absolutely right.
Let's not ruin this moment with words.

08:13.792 --> 08:15.667
‐ Oh, you've gotta be shitting me.

08:19.083 --> 08:21.708
♪ tense music playing ♪

08:21.708 --> 08:24.167
‐ Come on, little monkey.

08:24.167 --> 08:27.833
We're all dressed up
and ready to dance.

08:28.292 --> 08:29.500
SHINJI: What is it you want?

08:30.958 --> 08:32.083
Name your price.

08:32.083 --> 08:33.458
‐ Save your breath.

08:33.458 --> 08:37.667
I already work for you,
Prime Minister.

08:37.958 --> 08:40.458
Well, technically, I work
for Bonsai Master,

08:40.458 --> 08:42.042
but he worked for you.

08:42.417 --> 08:43.333
Right?

08:44.375 --> 08:45.875
Don't worry, boss.

08:46.375 --> 08:47.542
You're just bait.

08:47.958 --> 08:49.167
Monkey's here to kill you,

08:49.167 --> 08:50.667
and I'm here to kill Monkey.

08:51.167 --> 08:52.250
Once he's dead,

08:53.000 --> 08:55.417
your little secret
will be too.

08:55.958 --> 08:57.042
[groans]

08:57.042 --> 08:59.375
Now get back there, old man,

08:59.875 --> 09:02.292
before I lose my temper!

09:02.292 --> 09:03.125
[screeching]

09:04.875 --> 09:09.625
‐ [laughing]
You didn't think you could get away
from Silver Samurai, did you?

09:10.792 --> 09:12.292
‐ Holy shit! Where'd he go?

09:14.042 --> 09:14.625
[grunts]

09:15.917 --> 09:18.375
BRYCE: Sword!

09:20.667 --> 09:22.625
Okay, that was badass.

09:22.625 --> 09:23.292
[Monkey grunts]

09:23.292 --> 09:25.917
I mean, he definitely practiced it,
but still, you know, kudos.

09:26.583 --> 09:29.250
♪

09:37.042 --> 09:38.042
[electricity crackling]

09:39.500 --> 09:41.250
[laughs]

09:42.583 --> 09:45.833
♪

09:46.667 --> 09:48.167
[screeching]

09:48.625 --> 09:51.833
‐ Hey dude, we're running out
of real estate real quick here, man!

09:51.833 --> 09:54.000
[Monkey screeching]

09:58.208 --> 10:01.000
BRYCE: Ohhh, shit!

10:01.000 --> 10:02.000
[glass shatters]

10:02.000 --> 10:04.833
Whoa! Ho‐ho, yeah, man!

10:06.500 --> 10:07.708
[elevator bell dings]
‐ Huh?

10:10.417 --> 10:12.458
‐ Well, either that's a good sign

10:12.917 --> 10:14.583
or a really bad one.

10:15.208 --> 10:16.917
WOMAN: Don't go up there!

10:16.917 --> 10:18.625
She killed everybody!

10:21.833 --> 10:26.000
♪ elevator music playing ♪

10:29.167 --> 10:30.042
[Bryce sniffles]

10:31.625 --> 10:32.292
[bell dings]

10:33.125 --> 10:34.125
[swishing]

10:34.125 --> 10:35.042
[screeches]

10:35.292 --> 10:36.583
‐ Oh shit!

10:37.542 --> 10:38.667
LADY BULLSEYE: Hi there.

10:38.667 --> 10:40.542
So glad
you could join us.

10:40.958 --> 10:44.833
You know, our first meeting was
so incredibly irritating,

10:44.833 --> 10:47.458
but I'm sure
as a fellow professional

10:47.458 --> 10:51.667
you understand why I didn't want
to just call that a draw.

10:51.667 --> 10:53.167
‐ Oh crap, crap, crap!

10:53.500 --> 10:54.875
‐ Hey! Drop it!

10:56.792 --> 10:57.333
[screams]

11:01.917 --> 11:04.375
‐ Ugh. So annoying.

11:04.375 --> 11:07.042
♪ elevator music continues playing ♪

11:09.250 --> 11:12.917
♪

11:14.625 --> 11:17.042
[helicopter whirring]

11:17.042 --> 11:19.875
Here, little monkey‐monkey,

11:20.250 --> 11:23.042
Come out
and play‐ee‐yay.

11:23.875 --> 11:25.458
Ha‐ha‐ha‐ha! Ha!

11:26.458 --> 11:27.625
Ugh.
[hooting]

11:27.625 --> 11:28.750
Huh?

11:28.750 --> 11:29.583
[groans]

11:31.583 --> 11:33.083
Son of a bitch!

11:34.292 --> 11:35.167
[screeches]

11:35.167 --> 11:38.167
‐ Jesus Louisus! She's terrifying!

11:38.167 --> 11:40.958
‐ Now what did that priest say
about salt?

11:42.375 --> 11:44.208
Oh right!

11:46.750 --> 11:50.250
[groaning]

11:50.250 --> 11:51.958
[laughing]

11:52.542 --> 11:53.750
BRYCE: What the shit?

11:54.292 --> 11:56.417
‐ Hello, Bryce.

11:57.250 --> 11:58.792
‐ Oh my... Oh my god.

11:58.792 --> 12:00.875
[Lady Bullseye laughs]
I have physical form.

12:01.333 --> 12:02.542
Oh, and it hurts!

12:02.542 --> 12:04.625
‐ I remember you, Bryce.

12:05.167 --> 12:08.208
From that Goldman Sachs conference
back in 2011.

12:08.208 --> 12:09.208
‐ Dammit!

12:09.208 --> 12:10.458
‐ You hit on me.
[coughing]

12:10.917 --> 12:12.375
‐ Oh yeah.
Yeah, I'm remembering.

12:12.917 --> 12:13.875
Not my proudest moment.

12:13.875 --> 12:15.083
‐ As I remember,

12:15.083 --> 12:18.750
I got the target
and you got stood up.

12:18.750 --> 12:21.042
But this'll be fun‐‐

12:23.167 --> 12:25.250
[screeching]

12:27.042 --> 12:28.458
‐ You have to understand.

12:28.458 --> 12:30.208
I was frustrated with Ken.

12:30.417 --> 12:32.333
He was always
so impulsive.

12:32.333 --> 12:34.375
‐ What? What‐what‐what are you
talking about?

12:34.375 --> 12:37.583
Uncle, you are Prime Minister.
We gotta keep you safe.

12:37.583 --> 12:39.917
There's a helicopter on the roof.
Iymasho!

12:40.917 --> 12:42.208
[silverware clattering]

12:42.708 --> 12:44.167
LADY BULLSEYE:
Uh, uh, uh.

12:44.167 --> 12:45.583
[screeching]

12:46.333 --> 12:47.667
Where do you think you're going?

12:47.667 --> 12:49.208
[Monkey hooting]

12:49.208 --> 12:50.542
[laughs]

12:51.375 --> 12:53.542
‐ Ah, shit.
[Monkey screeching]

12:54.708 --> 12:56.208
Oww!

12:56.208 --> 12:58.625
Ow! Ow! Ow!

12:58.958 --> 13:00.500
[gasping]

13:01.792 --> 13:04.333
Oh ho. Come on.
You got this.

13:05.417 --> 13:07.500
Holy shit! That hurts!

13:09.042 --> 13:10.500
[Bryce screaming]

13:10.500 --> 13:12.917
‐ [chuckles]
Is that all you got?

13:12.917 --> 13:14.625
[maniacal laughter]

13:14.625 --> 13:16.208
[Monkey hooting]

13:16.208 --> 13:18.750
‐ Go! After them!
Save Akiko, man!

13:18.750 --> 13:19.750
[Monkey hooting]

13:19.750 --> 13:22.250
No, it's fine, okay.
We are a team!

13:22.875 --> 13:23.917
[Monkey grunts]

13:23.917 --> 13:27.208
‐ Ugh. You know, for a dead guy,
you look like shit.

13:27.958 --> 13:30.000
[grunting]

13:30.750 --> 13:31.958
[crunch]
[screams]

13:38.042 --> 13:41.542
LADY BULLSEYE:
Bryce, Bryce, Bryce.

13:42.042 --> 13:44.875
[groaning]

13:47.792 --> 13:51.750
You were always a worthless,
second‐rate assassin.

13:51.750 --> 13:52.792
‐ Can't argue with you there.

13:52.792 --> 13:55.917
But not so worthless
that I can't be a decent diversion.

13:57.792 --> 13:59.625
[gunshots]

13:59.625 --> 14:01.208
[clicking]

14:02.458 --> 14:03.917
[groans softly]

14:07.333 --> 14:08.292
[exhales sharply]

14:08.958 --> 14:11.167
‐ That was for Ito‐san.

14:13.125 --> 14:14.333
Oh, there is a ghost.

14:14.875 --> 14:16.458
‐ Oh. [laughs]

14:17.167 --> 14:18.250
Yeah. Hey.

14:20.250 --> 14:21.625
AKIKO: What the hell?

14:23.542 --> 14:24.958
Holy shit.

14:25.917 --> 14:26.417
‐ Stop.

14:26.958 --> 14:28.125
Akiko, stop.

14:28.583 --> 14:30.208
I have something
I have to tell you.

14:31.125 --> 14:32.625
I caused this.

14:32.625 --> 14:35.792
I'm responsible for all this death
and destruction.

14:36.375 --> 14:37.667
It was me.

14:37.667 --> 14:39.417
‐ Wha‐what? What was you?

14:39.417 --> 14:41.500
‐ Ken was losing the election!

14:42.208 --> 14:44.458
We were behind by ten points

14:44.458 --> 14:46.500
when we should
have been ahead by five!

14:47.417 --> 14:48.500
‐ What are you saying?

14:48.500 --> 14:50.208
‐ Bonsai Master approached me.

14:50.750 --> 14:53.167
He said that
Ken could be moved aside.

14:53.500 --> 14:55.917
That I could run
in Ken's place.

14:56.417 --> 14:58.625
That he would support
my agenda.

14:58.958 --> 15:01.667
Sure I'd have to make
a few concessions,

15:01.667 --> 15:04.542
but on all the things
we cared about,

15:04.875 --> 15:06.667
he would support us!

15:06.667 --> 15:08.333
I did it for the country!

15:09.208 --> 15:12.333
‐ You... killed Ken?

15:12.333 --> 15:14.125
‐ I did a horrible thing.

15:14.792 --> 15:17.208
And the worst thing is,
it worked.

15:17.750 --> 15:21.042
But then,
everyone started dying.

15:21.500 --> 15:23.542
And this monkey came back.

15:24.167 --> 15:25.833
It's all gotten out of hand.

15:25.833 --> 15:27.000
[Monkey hooting]

15:30.583 --> 15:33.333
You have come for me,
haven't you, Monkey?

15:33.917 --> 15:35.542
[growls]

15:36.333 --> 15:36.917
‐ Wait...

15:36.917 --> 15:39.708
‐ You are the spirit of vengeance,

15:40.375 --> 15:42.917
come to punish me
for my sins.

15:42.917 --> 15:45.042
‐ No! Monkey, no!

15:46.167 --> 15:47.708
You don't have to do this.

15:47.708 --> 15:48.625
[growls]

15:49.250 --> 15:50.542
‐ No, Monkey!

15:50.542 --> 15:52.458
Killing him is not the way!

15:52.458 --> 15:55.208
He deserves to stand trial
in front of the country.

15:55.208 --> 15:56.083
‐ Don't do it, pal.

15:56.083 --> 15:57.708
[hooting]

15:57.708 --> 15:59.500
Look, I've made
this mistake before, okay.

15:59.500 --> 16:00.750
Akiko won't forgive you.

16:00.750 --> 16:02.083
‐ Is that a ghost?

16:02.083 --> 16:04.125
[screeching]

16:04.125 --> 16:07.208
‐ I know, I know it'll cost me
a chance of ascending.

16:07.208 --> 16:09.625
And we won't get the person responsible
for all this shit.

16:09.625 --> 16:13.375
But there's‐‐ there's something tells me
that killing this selfish prick

16:13.375 --> 16:14.667
isn't the answer.

16:14.667 --> 16:18.583
And‐and‐and I know it won't give me
any kind of happy ending,

16:18.583 --> 16:22.083
but I‐‐ Look, I'm willing to forgo that,
in order for you,

16:22.458 --> 16:24.042
for you to have the happy ending.

16:28.417 --> 16:29.792
Oh shit, wha‐‐

16:29.792 --> 16:31.500
Oh for‐‐ Now what?

16:32.792 --> 16:34.542
Oh! Holy shit.

16:35.792 --> 16:38.917
Hey! Hey, hey, look!
Look, I'm ascending!

16:39.375 --> 16:40.667
Oh my god!

16:40.667 --> 16:42.083
[laughs] Oh!

16:42.083 --> 16:45.042
Oh, I get it.
I had to do the right thing.

16:45.500 --> 16:48.208
Oh, that's what Baldy meant
by removing the seed of evil.

16:48.208 --> 16:50.583
It was like,
the barren field was me.

16:50.583 --> 16:53.333
I‐‐ Ha ha!
Oh, that cryptic jerk.

16:53.917 --> 16:57.167
Holy shit. Oh, shit‐‐
Hey! Uh, Monkey!

16:57.792 --> 16:59.917
Monkey. Look, I think‐‐

16:59.917 --> 17:02.042
I think you know
how I feel about you, okay.

17:02.042 --> 17:04.458
And I'm sorry
for ruining your life.

17:05.000 --> 17:07.167
Just take care
of yourself, alright?

17:08.250 --> 17:11.000
And remember to drink
plenty of water!

17:13.750 --> 17:14.667
[whines]

17:15.292 --> 17:16.625
‐ Shinji Yokohama,

17:16.625 --> 17:19.583
I'm placing you under arrest
for the murder of Ken Takahara.

17:19.583 --> 17:20.500
[handcuff click]

17:21.750 --> 17:23.583
SHINJI: It can't end like this.

17:27.833 --> 17:30.000
Ken's death
will not be in vain.

17:38.583 --> 17:40.500
AKIKO: No!

17:41.500 --> 17:42.875
Oh!

17:45.333 --> 17:48.458
What did you do,
you animal?

17:52.458 --> 17:53.708
‐ How did he get my gun?

17:55.667 --> 17:57.500
[Akiko sobs]

17:57.500 --> 18:00.292
‐ He was the only family I had!

18:00.958 --> 18:03.042
God damn you!

18:06.208 --> 18:07.792
‐ Monkey, you have
to get out of here.

18:07.792 --> 18:09.000
[hooting]

18:09.000 --> 18:11.208
No, Monkey, you've just shot
the Prime Minister!

18:11.583 --> 18:13.833
Trust me,
you have to leave!

18:17.833 --> 18:18.917
[whimpers]

18:18.917 --> 18:22.667
♪

18:30.083 --> 18:34.542
♪ melancholy music playing ♪

18:34.542 --> 18:38.208
♪

18:46.833 --> 18:50.542
♪

18:50.542 --> 18:52.500
‐ May the road rise
to meet you.

18:54.667 --> 18:57.125
May the wind be
always at your back.

18:57.833 --> 19:00.625
May the sun shine warm
upon your face.

19:01.583 --> 19:02.208
May the rain

19:03.250 --> 19:05.333
fall softly upon your fields

19:05.833 --> 19:08.500
until we meet again.

19:08.500 --> 19:10.958
♪

19:11.458 --> 19:13.708
[airplane whooshing]

19:16.750 --> 19:20.083
♪

19:37.125 --> 19:42.000
♪

19:42.667 --> 19:44.500
Hi, guys. Nice to see you.

19:44.958 --> 19:45.875
Yep.

19:46.375 --> 19:48.458
Thank you.
Good to see you.

19:53.250 --> 19:54.708
I'm going to make this right.

19:55.250 --> 19:56.917
I will clear your name.

19:56.917 --> 19:59.125
[grunting]

19:59.542 --> 20:00.542
I promise you.

20:00.542 --> 20:02.333
[hooting]

20:02.333 --> 20:04.000
Yes, I put a juice box in there.

20:04.000 --> 20:05.542
You told me, like, six times.

20:12.708 --> 20:16.958
♪

20:23.875 --> 20:25.042
[sighs]

20:25.833 --> 20:27.333
BRYCE: Mm, mm, mm.
[Monkey grunts]

20:28.667 --> 20:29.542
‐ Huh?

20:31.583 --> 20:34.292
‐ I can't tell you how happy
this whole image makes me.

20:34.292 --> 20:37.708
[hooting]

20:37.708 --> 20:38.875
Well, here's what happened.

20:38.875 --> 20:40.333
Uh, you know,
I got to the afterlife,

20:40.333 --> 20:42.625
and it was
an awesome place.

20:42.625 --> 20:44.917
You know? Fire everywhere.
Super dramatic.

20:44.917 --> 20:47.125
Uh, you know,
little bit like Reno, but better.

20:47.125 --> 20:47.958
‐ Ahh!

20:47.958 --> 20:50.250
‐ Slayer playing.
Dragons everywhere.

20:50.250 --> 20:51.375
Really fun.

20:51.375 --> 20:52.667
And I was like, psyched.

20:52.667 --> 20:55.458
But I thought, "You know what?
As great as this place is,"

20:55.458 --> 20:57.167
and it was great, really.

20:57.167 --> 21:00.083
I was like, you know what?
My friend's up there all alone,

21:00.083 --> 21:01.708
still kind of learning
the ropes.

21:01.708 --> 21:04.083
Uh, lots more killers to kill,
if you know what I mean.

21:04.083 --> 21:05.750
And I think
he needs my help.

21:05.750 --> 21:08.375
Anyway, the red dude,
he agreed, you know.

21:08.375 --> 21:10.625
Made me sign a contract,
which I didn't read but who cares.

21:10.625 --> 21:12.333
I mean, how's he ever gonna
hold me to it, right?

21:12.333 --> 21:13.417
[Monkey groans]

21:13.417 --> 21:15.125
So I figure, you know,
we go to New York.

21:15.125 --> 21:16.167
I have a great handler.

21:16.167 --> 21:17.917
She, uh, she books me
on all my gigs,

21:17.917 --> 21:20.083
and‐and right after we put
the fear of God in her

21:20.083 --> 21:21.292
for booking me on this one,

21:21.292 --> 21:23.167
she'll definitely want
to take you on as a client.

21:23.167 --> 21:26.125
Then we can earn some real coin.
You know what I mean?

21:26.125 --> 21:26.708
[Monkey grunts]

21:26.708 --> 21:28.875
Kill a whole bunch of assholes
who deserve to die

21:28.875 --> 21:29.917
and maybe, uh,

21:30.292 --> 21:31.708
you know, see the sights.

21:32.208 --> 21:34.542
Oh, oh, by the way,
check this out. Look at this.

21:37.708 --> 21:39.875
[screeching]

21:39.875 --> 21:41.000
I know, right?

21:41.000 --> 21:42.917
I mean, I figure
this could come in pretty handy.

21:43.750 --> 21:47.208
Yeah, you know I picked up
a few things from Yuki. You know?

21:47.208 --> 21:49.625
Ol' Brycey's back
in action, huh?

21:49.625 --> 21:51.083
Here, let me clean
that up for you.

21:55.083 --> 21:56.083
[Monkey grunts]

21:57.625 --> 22:00.375
Yeah. I mean, I'm still working on it.
[bottle rattles]

22:00.375 --> 22:02.167
You know, ten‐thousand hours.
[chuckles]

22:02.750 --> 22:05.083
That's what that, uh,
Gladwell said, right?

22:06.583 --> 22:07.625
[grunting]

